<subSubSection id="C31CD2F88E608041A0B1A49CFB563E41" pageId="3" pageNumber="576" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BB981738E608041A0B1A49CFB563E41" blockId="3.[151,1436,1683,1841]" pageId="3" pageNumber="576">
<emphasis id="B9725D618E608041A0B1A49CFED33FDD" bold="true" box="[151,273,1683,1708]" pageId="3" pageNumber="576">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C06FAF08E608041A13EA49CFE2A3FDA" authority="Siewert &amp; Madruga &amp; Dolibaina &amp; Mielke &amp; Casagrande, 2018" authorityName="Siewert &amp; Madruga &amp; Dolibaina &amp; Mielke &amp; Casagrande" authorityYear="2018" box="[280,488,1683,1708]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Drephalys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="576" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="citrinus" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="B9725D618E608041A13EA49CFE2A3FDA" box="[280,488,1683,1708]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="576">Drephalys citrinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A241E01A8E608041A1C9A49CFDED3FDD" box="[495,559,1683,1708]" pageId="3" pageNumber="576" rank="species">
<emphasis id="B9725D618E608041A1C9A49CFDED3FDD" bold="true" box="[495,559,1683,1708]" pageId="3" pageNumber="576">sp. n.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
is nearly identical to 
<taxonomicName id="4C06FAF08E608041A306A49BFBB13FDD" authority="(Hewitson, 1867)" authorityName="Hewitson" authorityYear="1867" baseAuthorityName="Hewitson" baseAuthorityYear="1867" box="[800,1139,1683,1708]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Drephalys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="576" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="phoenice">
<emphasis id="B9725D618E608041A306A49BFC6A3FDD" box="[800,936,1683,1708]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="576">D. phoenice</emphasis>
(Hewitson, 1867)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C06FAF08E608041A48FA49BFA823FDD" authorityName="Bell" authorityYear="1942" box="[1193,1344,1683,1708]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Drephalys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="576" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="heraclides">
<emphasis id="B9725D618E608041A48FA49BFA823FDD" box="[1193,1344,1683,1708]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="576">D. heraclides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in wing markings and in the wider white transversal band on the ventral hind wings. It is distinguished from 
<taxonomicName id="4C06FAF08E608041A4D5A4BAFAB83FBC" baseAuthorityName="Hewitson" baseAuthorityYear="1867" box="[1267,1402,1716,1741]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Drephalys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="576" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="phoenice">
<emphasis id="B9725D618E608041A4D5A4BAFAB83FBC" box="[1267,1402,1716,1741]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="576">D. phoenice</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the reduced lilac reflections on the ventral wings, and from 
<taxonomicName id="4C06FAF08E608041A363A4D9FC1C3F9F" authorityName="Bell" authorityYear="1942" box="[837,990,1749,1774]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Drephalys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="576" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="heraclides">
<emphasis id="B9725D618E608041A363A4D9FC1C3F9F" box="[837,990,1749,1774]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="576">D. heraclides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the white band almost reaching the costal margin. Furthermore, 
<taxonomicName id="4C06FAF08E608041A1FFA4F7FD903E7E" authority="Siewert &amp; Madruga &amp; Dolibaina &amp; Mielke &amp; Casagrande, 2018" authorityName="Siewert &amp; Madruga &amp; Dolibaina &amp; Mielke &amp; Casagrande" authorityYear="2018" box="[473,594,1784,1807]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Drephalys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="576" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="citrinus" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="B9725D618E608041A1FFA4F7FD903E7E" box="[473,594,1784,1807]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="576">D. citrinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A241E01A8E608041A27CA4F9FD593E7E" box="[602,667,1782,1807]" pageId="3" pageNumber="576" rank="species">
<emphasis id="B9725D618E608041A27CA4F9FD593E7E" bold="true" box="[602,667,1782,1807]" pageId="3" pageNumber="576">sp. n.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
has a short uncus, with truncate arms, and not deeply bifid as in 
<taxonomicName id="4C06FAF08E608041A5A7A4F7FF3E3E40" baseAuthorityName="Hewitson" baseAuthorityYear="1867" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Drephalys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="576" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="phoenice">
<emphasis id="B9725D618E608041A5A7A4F7FF3E3E40" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="576">D. phoenice</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="133D9DF68E608041A12DA517FE9E3E41" box="[267,348,1816,1841]" captionStart="FIGURES 10–12" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1268,1291]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1248]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,193,1248]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 10–12. Male genitalia of Drephalys species. Structures as presented in figures 7–9. 10. D. heraclides. 11. D. phoenice. 12. D. phoenicoides." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1440355/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="576">Fig. 11</figureCitation>
), and the costa of the valva has a short and narrow distal process (
<figureCitation id="133D9DF68E608041A464A517FB443E41" box="[1090,1158,1816,1841]" captionStart="FIGURES 7–9" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1161,1184]" captionTargetBox="[151,1437,199,1143]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1437,199,1143]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 7–9. Male genitalia of Drephalys species. Tegumen, uncus, gnathos and saccus in lateral view; right valva in left, right and dorsal views; tegumen and uncus in dorsal view; aedeagus in left lateral and dorsal views; detail of the everted cornuti. 7. D. dracarys sp. n., 8. D. electrinus sp. n., 9. D. citrinus sp. n." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1440353/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="576">Fig. 9</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
