<subSubSection id="C31CD2F88E668047A0E1A759FE463FFE" pageId="5" pageNumber="578" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BB981738E668047A0E1A759FE463FFE" blockId="5.[151,1436,1366,1679]" pageId="5" pageNumber="578">
<emphasis id="B9725D618E668047A0E1A759FE8D3C1E" bold="true" box="[199,335,1366,1391]" pageId="5" pageNumber="578">Comments.</emphasis>
The arm of the gnathos ribbed at the tip of 
<taxonomicName id="4C06FAF08E668047A352A759FB883C1E" authority="Siewert &amp; Madruga &amp; Dolibaina &amp; Mielke &amp; Casagrande, 2018" authorityName="Siewert &amp; Madruga &amp; Dolibaina &amp; Mielke &amp; Casagrande" authorityYear="2018" box="[884,1098,1366,1391]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Drephalys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="578" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="citrinus" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="B9725D618E668047A352A759FB883C1E" box="[884,1098,1366,1391]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="578">Drephalys citrinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A241E01A8E668047A470A759FB5E3C1E" box="[1110,1180,1366,1391]" pageId="5" pageNumber="578" rank="species">
<emphasis id="B9725D618E668047A470A759FB5E3C1E" bold="true" box="[1110,1180,1366,1391]" pageId="5" pageNumber="578">sp. n.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
is also present in 
<taxonomicName id="4C06FAF08E668047A5A7A757FECE3CE2" authorityName="Bell" authorityYear="1942" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Drephalys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="578" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="heraclides">
<emphasis id="B9725D618E668047A5A7A757FECE3CE2" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="578">D. heraclides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, suggesting the latter is a close relative of the former. 
<taxonomicName id="4C06FAF08E668047A34BA773FC273CE2" authority="Siewert &amp; Madruga &amp; Dolibaina &amp; Mielke &amp; Casagrande, 2018" authorityName="Siewert &amp; Madruga &amp; Dolibaina &amp; Mielke &amp; Casagrande" authorityYear="2018" box="[877,997,1404,1427]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Drephalys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="578" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="citrinus" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="B9725D618E668047A34BA773FC273CE2" box="[877,997,1404,1427]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="578">D. citrinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A241E01A8E668047A3CAA775FBEE3CE2" box="[1004,1068,1402,1427]" pageId="5" pageNumber="578" rank="species">
<emphasis id="B9725D618E668047A3CAA775FBEE3CE2" bold="true" box="[1004,1068,1402,1427]" pageId="5" pageNumber="578">sp. n.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
, together with 
<taxonomicName id="4C06FAF08E668047A4F3A773FAAF3CE2" authorityName="Bell" authorityYear="1942" box="[1237,1389,1402,1427]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Drephalys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="578" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="heraclides">
<emphasis id="B9725D618E668047A4F3A773FAAF3CE2" box="[1237,1389,1402,1427]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="578">D. heraclides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C06FAF08E668047A0B1A7AFFE523CC6" authority="Evans, 1952" authorityName="Evans" authorityYear="1952" box="[151,400,1438,1463]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Drephalys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="578" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="opifex">
<emphasis id="B9725D618E668047A0B1A7AFFF3F3CC6" box="[151,253,1439,1463]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="578">D. opifex</emphasis>
Evans, 1952
</taxonomicName>
, are the only yellow-checkered species belonging to the subgenus 
<taxonomicName id="4C06FAF08E668047A454A791FB243CC6" authorityName="Watson" authorityYear="1893" box="[1138,1254,1438,1463]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Drephalys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="578" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9725D618E668047A454A791FB243CC6" box="[1138,1254,1438,1463]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="578">Drephalys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
without a costal fold on the forewing (
<figureCitation id="133D9DF68E668047A1B5A7CDFE1B3CAA" box="[403,473,1474,1499]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–6" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1765,1788]" captionTargetBox="[198,1387,221,1717]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[198,1388,198,1717]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–6. Species of Drephalys in dorsal and ventral views. 1–2, D. dracarys sp. n. 3–4, D. electrinus sp. n. 5–6, D. citrinus sp. n." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1440351/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="578">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
). The absence of the forewing costal fold in this subgenus is also shared by 
<taxonomicName id="4C06FAF08E668047A56EA7CBFEE03C8E" authority="Evans, 1952" authorityName="Evans" authorityYear="1952" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Drephalys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="578" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="olva">
<emphasis id="B9725D618E668047A56EA7CBFA5E3CAA" box="[1352,1436,1474,1499]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="578">D. olva</emphasis>
Evans, 1952
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C06FAF08E668047A17CA7E7FD9A3C8E" authority="Evans, 1952" authorityName="Evans" authorityYear="1952" box="[346,600,1510,1535]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Drephalys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="578" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="olvina">
<emphasis id="B9725D618E668047A17CA7E7FE013C8E" box="[346,451,1510,1535]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="578">D. olvina</emphasis>
Evans, 1952
</taxonomicName>
, while 
<taxonomicName id="4C06FAF08E668047A28CA7E7FC703C8E" authority="Burns, 2000" authorityName="Burns" authorityYear="2000" box="[682,946,1510,1535]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Drephalys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="578" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kidonoi">
<emphasis id="B9725D618E668047A28CA7E7FCE33C8E" box="[682,801,1510,1535]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="578">D. kidonoi</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EF97FC828E668047A30EA7E7FC703C8E" box="[808,946,1511,1535]" pageId="5" pageNumber="578" refId="ref4060" refString="Burns, J. M. &amp; Janzen, D. H. (2000) Drephalys: division of this showy Neotropical genus, plus a new species and the immatures and food plants of two species from Costa Rican dry forest (Hesperiidae: Pyrginae). Journal of the Lepidopterists' Society, 53, 77 - 89." type="journal article">Burns, 2000</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
has a vestigial costal fold (
<bibRefCitation id="EF97FC828E668047A4C0A7E8FF163F52" pageId="5" pageNumber="578" refId="ref4060" refString="Burns, J. M. &amp; Janzen, D. H. (2000) Drephalys: division of this showy Neotropical genus, plus a new species and the immatures and food plants of two species from Costa Rican dry forest (Hesperiidae: Pyrginae). Journal of the Lepidopterists' Society, 53, 77 - 89." type="journal article">Burns &amp; Janzen 2000</bibRefCitation>
). The evaluation of this character is useful to differentiate the males of species with similar wing phenotypes, as is the case with species possessing yellow spots on the dorsal wings. However, studies of other features are required for species-level determinations, such as the development of the ventral hind wing white band and details of the male genitalia.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
